  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "As soon as she finished her university degree at Leeds she went on Aliyah and has now lived for 18 months in Israel, first in Haifa, now in Jerusalem.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "And she's working for the youth movement, the reform movement in the education side of children.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "And she's very much into Zionism, Judaism, Holocaust, et cetera, et cetera, as long as it's not ultra-orthodoxy.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "That's the only thing she hates.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "And she's here and you'll be able to see her later on.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it is, really.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the book that I'm writing, I hope you don't pinch the title, is because I feel that it is not a unique achievement, but quite an achievement to come from the depth of Belsen to the peak of Buckingham Palace, in my opinion anyway.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "For me it is a tremendous achievement.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I'm-- I'm very proud of it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I don't know why I got the MBE.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But then, I don't know why I went to Belsen, except for [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So basically, the Buckingham Palace thing was that we first received a letter from the Prime Minister, dropped to a letter box on the 11th of the 11th in 1989, not exactly 11 o'clock, but almost on Armistice Day, Armistice Hour.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it was addressed to me and it said top secret and all this from Her-- from the Prime Minister's office and all that kind of stuff.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I couldn't believe it was for me.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I thought it was for Corinne.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Anyway, I opened it and it said that the Prime Minister has it in mind to award the MBE.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "If you're agreeable, would you please fill in this form, you know?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So I was very impressed that she was thinking about me, [INAUDIBLE] this in mind, Mrs.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Thatcher.",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
